## 2. The attribution decision rule (pre-registered)

```
Let:
    signal_ratio = |K_G| / bacl_predicted_noise_floor
    e_safe       = E_log2_base_operand > log2(1e-4) ≈ -13.3

Decision:
    if E is computable AND e_safe is False:
        attribution = format_precision_pinned, confidence = 0.0

    elif signal_ratio > 1000:
        attribution = phenomenon
        confidence = min(1, log10(signal_ratio) / 16)

    elif signal_ratio > 1:
        attribution = ambiguous
        confidence = 0.5

    else:
        attribution = substrate
        confidence = min(1, 1 - signal_ratio)
```

Thresholds (`1e3`, `1.0`, `log2(1e-4)`) are pre-registered. Phase F does not adjust them post-hoc.

